==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Developable
<hw>De*vel"op*a*ble</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>a.</pos> <def>Capable of
being developed.</def> <rj><au>J. Peile.</au></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><cs><col><b>Developable surface</b></col> <fld>(Math.)</fld>, <cd>a
surface described by a moving right line, and such that consecutive
positions of the generator intersect each other. Hence, the surface can
be developed into a plane.</cd></cs>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>developed</ent>⟦br⟧
